---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import AvaniFloorPlan from "@assets/venue/avaniFloorPlan.png";
import BtsToAvani from "@assets/venue/btsToAvani.png";
import AppStoreLogo from "@assets/venue/appStore.png";
import PlayStoreLogo from "@assets/venue/playStore.png";

const bangkokURL =
  "https://a.cdn-hotels.com/gdcs/production22/d1769/8f94419d-5e5a-44c5-82fc-fc26eb1a9767.jpg?impolicy=fcrop&w=800&h=533&q=medium";
const avaniURL =
  "https://ak-d.tripcdn.com/images/1mi582234acf28vhs1736.jpg?proc=source/trip";
const venuemapURL = `https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/embed?mid=1F19ofRc39I04Z9zexW91goEBM0x9XZU&ehbc=2E312F&noprof=1`;
const mrtbtsURL =
  "https://travelhappy.info/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Bangkok-BTS-MRT-Map-2021.png";
const btsexitURL =
  "https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-nDdV-Ddij_4/YAWZqwzPl7I/AAAAAAAFI-A/KFd97ZoN0ioPMK8gVJcUL7xlpLH5s-ylgCLcBGAsYHQ/s800/20210113_104722.jpg";
const directionURL = "https://maps.app.goo.gl/tWZ7VpbXEoFXcQWk8";
const grabAndroidURL =
  "https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.grabtaxi.passenger&hl=en&gl=US";
const grabIosURL =
  "https://apps.apple.com/sg/app/grab-taxi-food-delivery/id647268330";
const bkkRailAndroid = "https://play.google.com/store/search?q=bkk+rail&c=apps";
const bkkRailiOS = "https://apps.apple.com/sg/app/bkk-rail/id1448681649";
const arlticketURL =
  "https://theexclusivetransfer.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/people-at-the-airport-rail-link-station.webp";
const dmksignURL =
  "https://photos.smugmug.com/Asia/Thailand/Bangkok-Don-Muang-Airport/i-S8SmHd5/0/934af571/L/20230302_131617-to-srt-red-line-L.jpg";
const dmkwayURL =
  "https://photos.smugmug.com/Asia/Thailand/Bangkok-Don-Muang-Airport/i-cBm9gHB/0/1c991736/L/20230302_131748-walkway-to-station-L.jpg";
const dmkcommuURL =
  "https://photos.smugmug.com/Future-Southeast-Asia/Thailand/Bangkok-Transport/i-Rf5bfS8/0/c2614bcb/L/20230302_124719-don-muang-commuter-and-long-distance-L.jpg";
const dmkdarkredURL =
  "https://pmk.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Untitled-3-1.jpg";

//   const avaniFloorPan = '/images/avaniFloorPan.png'
---

<Layout title="PyCon TH 2023 - Venue">
  <div class="mx-auto flex w-full flex-col px-6 md:px-16">
    <ul
      class="menu menu-horizontal sticky top-0 w-full justify-center bg-white"
    >
      <li>
        <details>
          <summary class="w-[250px]">Venue</summary>
          <ul class="venue-menu z-10 bg-white">
            <li>
              <a href="#bangkok">
                <Icon name="solar:city-bold" />
                Bangkok
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="#avani">
                <Icon name="mdi:location" />
                Avani Sukhumvit
              </a>
              <ul class="sub-menu">
                <li>
                  <a href="#pyconmap">
                    <Icon name="material-symbols:map-outline" />
                    Map - Avani
                  </a>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </li>
      <li>
        <details>
          <summary class="w-[240px] pb-0">Transportation</summary>
          <ul class="venue-menu bg-white">
            <li>
              <a href="#toAvani"><Icon name="mdi:location" />Getting to Avani</a
              >
              <ul class="sub-menu">
                <li>
                  <a href="#btsAvani"
                    ><Icon name="material-symbols:train-outline" />BTS Skytrain</a
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="#mrtAvani"
                    ><Icon name="material-symbols:subway-outline" />MRT Subway</a
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="#parkingAvani"
                    ><Icon name="mdi:car-outline" />Driving and Parking</a
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="#grabAvani"
                    ><Icon name="simple-icons:grab" />Grab (Uber)</a
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <a href="#airportAvani"
                    ><Icon name="uil:plane-fly" />Airport</a
                  >
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div id="venue">
      <div class="mb-4 flex">
        <h1
          class="bg-header-orange px-2 py-2 text-2xl font-bold uppercase text-white lg:text-4xl"
        >
          Venue
        </h1>
      </div>
      <h2 id="bangkok" class="scroll-mt-14 text-lg font-bold text-primary">
        Bangkok
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Bangkok is the capital of Thailand and one of the most popular tourist
        destinations in Southeast Asia. It is a city of contrasts, with the
        coexistence of temples and modern skyscrapers. Bangkok is also known for
        its vibrant street food scene and friendly people.
      </p>
      <img
        src={bangkokURL}
        class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
      />
    </div>
    <h2 id="avani" class="scroll-mt-14 text-lg font-bold text-primary">
      Avani Sukhumvit
    </h2>
    <p>
      Our conference event on the 7th floor of Avani Sukhumvit, the first
      upscale 5-star hotel in the area. Enjoy stylish rooms with city skyline
      views, complemented by cutting-edge tech features in a top-tier event
      venue. Located at 2089 Sukhumvit Road, Phra Khanong Nuea, Watthana,
      Bangkok 10260, Thailand.
    </p>
    <img
      src={avaniURL}
      class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
    />
  </div>
  <!-- <img src={avaniFloorPan} class='place-content-center md:w-1/2 h-auto mx-auto mb-4 mt-4'></img> -->
  <div class="flex w-full justify-center">
    <Image src={AvaniFloorPlan} alt="Avani's floor plan" />
  </div>
  <div id="pyconmap" class="mb-8 mt-8 scroll-mt-14">
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3876.2179746118977!2d100.59906201124203!3d13.705244086626234!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x30e29f5881f210f9%3A0xe614ba9d6cbc85b2!2sAvani%20Sukhumvit%20Bangkok!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sth!4v1699348120687!5m2!1sen!2sth"
        width="640"
        height="480"
        loading="lazy"></iframe>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
<div id="transportation">
  <div class="mb-3 mt-5 flex">
    <h2
      class="bg-header-orange px-2 py-2 text-2xl font-bold uppercase text-white lg:text-4xl"
    >
      Transportation
    </h2>
  </div>
  <div id="toAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
    <p class="mb-2 text-lg font-bold text-primary">
      Getting to Avani Sukhumvit
    </p>
  </div>
  <p class="mb-3 flex">
    There are several transportation options available in Bangkok. We recommend
    the following five methods of travel which are known for being fast, easy,
    and safe for traveling in Bangkok. We generally do not recommend traveling
    by car or bus as traffic in Bangkok is unpredicatble.
  </p>
  <div id="btsAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
    <h3 class="text-md mb-2 font-bold text-primary">BTS Skytrain</h3>
    <p>
      Taking BTS Skytrain is the fastest and easiest way to get to the venue.
    </p>
    <p>
      Avani Sukhumvit is directly connected to the BTS Skytrain the Sukhumvit
      Line (Green Line) On-nut Station via Exit 3. To get to the venue from the
      station, you can follow these steps:
    </p>
    <ul class="mb-4 mt-4 list-inside list-decimal space-y-4">
      <li>
        Take MTR Subway the Sukhumvit Line (Blue Line) to Sukhumvit Station,
        which is connected to the BTS Skytrain at Asok Station.
      </li>
      <li>Transfer to the BTS Skytrain and take it to On Nut Station.</li>
      <li>
        Exit the station at Exit 3 and follow the signs to Avani Sukhumvit
        Bangkok.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <Image
      src={BtsToAvani}
      class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
      alt="Bts to Avani"
    />
  </div>
  <div id="mrtAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
    <h3 class="text-md font-bold text-primary">MRT Subway</h3>
    <p>To get to Avani Sukhumvit Bangkok by MRT, you can follow these steps:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-inside list-decimal space-y-2">
      <li>
        Take MTR Subway the Sukhumvit Line (Blue Line) to Sukhumvit Station,
        which is connected to the BTS Skytrain at Asok Station. The map below
        illustrates how the stations are connected, which can help you navigate
        the transportation system more easily.
      </li>
      <img
        src={mrtbtsURL}
        class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
      />
    </ul>
    <li>Transfer to the BTS Skytrain and take it to On Nut Station.</li>
    <li>
      After arriving at On Nut Station, take the Exit 3 and follow the signs to
      Avani Sukhumvit Bangkok.
    </li>
    <img
      src={btsexitURL}
      class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
    />
  </div>
</div>
<h3 class="mt-3">
  Note: There's also an App that tells you how to get from station A to station
  B with estimate time and cost
</h3>
<div class="flex items-center">
  <a href={bkkRailAndroid} class="text-blue-500">
    <Image src={PlayStoreLogo} height={75} alt="BKK Rail Android App" />
  </a>
  |
  <a href={bkkRailiOS} class="text-blue-500">
    <Image src={AppStoreLogo} height={60} class="p-2" alt="BKK Rail iOS App" />
  </a>
</div>

<div id="parkingAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
  <h3 class="text-md font-bold text-primary">Driving and Parking</h3>
  <p>Parking at Avani Sukhumvit is free all day for guests.</p>
  <p>
    <a href={directionURL} class="text-blue-500"> Google Map Direction </a>
  </p>
</div>
<div id="grabAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
  <h3 class="text-md font-bold text-primary">Grab (Uber) / Taxi</h3>
  <p>
    To travel in Bangkok by car or motorcycle, we recommend using Grab (Uber).
    Grab is a ride-hailing app that is widely used in Thailand and is a
    convenient and reliable way to get around it’s allowed you to track your
    fares and journey. You can also order food via Grab.
  </p>
  <ul class="mb-4 mt-4 list-inside list-disc space-y-4">
    <li>
      Tell the driver to go to <strong>Avani Sukhumvit Bangkok Hotel.</strong>
    </li>
    <li>
      The ride should take around 30 minutes to 1 hour from Suvarnabhumi
      Airport.
    </li>
    <li>The ride should take around 30 to 45 minutes from the city center.</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="flex items-center">
    <a href={grabAndroidURL} class="text-blue-500">
      <Image src={PlayStoreLogo} height={75} alt="Grab Android App" />
    </a>
    |
    <a href={grabIosURL} class="text-blue-500">
      <Image src={AppStoreLogo} height={60} class="p-2" alt="Grab iOS App" />
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
<div id="airportAvani" class="mb-4 mt-4 scroll-mt-14 space-y-2">
  <h3 class="text-md mb-2 font-bold text-primary">Airport</h3>
  <p>
    Bangkok is served by two airports, Suvarnabhumi Airport and Don Mueang
    International Airport. Both airports offer various transportation options to
    get to the venue.
  </p>
  <h3 class="text-md mb-2 mt-2 font-bold text-primary">Suvarnabhumi Airport</h3>
  <p>
    To get to the venue from Suvarnabhumi Airport, we reccommend using Grab or
    taking Airport Rail Link Skytrain (ARL Red Line).
  </p>
  <ul class="mb-4 mt-4 list-inside list-decimal space-y-2">
    <li>
      Go down to the basement level and get the Airport Rail Link (ARL) Skytrain
      to BTS Skytrain Phaya Thai Station (45 baht, terminal station).
    </li>
    <img
      src={arlticketURL}
      class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
    />
  </ul>
  <li>
    The whole journey takes about 90 minutes. Trains stop running at midnight.
  </li>
  <li>
    After arriving and tranfer to the Phaya Thai BTS Skytrain, you can take the
    same line of BTS to get to venue to On Nut Station. see
    <a href="#btsAvani" class="mx-2 text-blue-500"> BTS Skytrain Guide </a>
    for details
  </li>
</div>
<h3 class="text-md mb-4 font-bold text-primary">Don Mueng Airport</h3>
<p class="mb-2">
  If you're taking a domestic or regional flight, you may be coming from Don
  Mueang airport. To get to the venue, we reccommend using Grab or taking
  Airport Link Skytrain (Dark Red Line).
</p>
<p>
  Don Mueang Airport is also connected to the Airport Link Skytrain (Dark Red
  Line) but the train from Don Mueang airport is connected to MTR Subway not BTS
  Skytrain
</p>
<ul class="mb-4 mt-4 list-inside list-decimal">
  <li>
    To get to the station, follow the signs to SRT Red Line. It is not referred
    to as “Airport Train” on the signs.
  </li>
  <img
    src={dmksignURL}
    class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
  />
</ul>
<li>
  There is a step-free walkway that connects the airport to the station on the
  other side of a massive highway.
</li>
<img
  src={dmkwayURL}
  class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
/>
<li>
  At the station, you are presented with two options; Long Distance and
  Commuter. For trains to Bangkok, you need the commuter.
</li>
<img
  src={dmkcommuURL}
  class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
/>
<li>
  The Commuter Line is operated by the State Railways of Thailand. Tickets are
  in the form of a token. You need to buy ticket to Bang Sue Grand Station.
</li>
<img
  src={dmkdarkredURL}
  class="mx-auto mb-4 mt-4 h-auto place-content-center md:w-1/2"
/>
<li>
  After arriving at Bang Sue Grand Station, there are signs at the Commuter Line
  exits that direct you to the MRT Blue Line under the station then you have to
  take the MRT to venue, see
  <a href="#mrtAvani" class="mx-2 text-blue-500"> MRT Subway Guide </a>
  for details
</li>
